N move toward DOOKU.Â OBI-WAN: You won&#39;t get away this time, Dooku.Â OBI-WAN and ANAKIN charge COUNT DOOKU. A great sword fight ensues.Â COUNT DOOKU: I&#39;ve been looking forward to this.Â ANAKIN: My powers have doubled since the last time we met, Count.Â COUNT DOOKU: Good. Twice the pride, double the fall.Â DOOKU lunges at the JEDI and they fall back . . .Â COUNT DOOKU: (continuing) Your moves are clumsy, Kenobi . . . too predictable. You&#39;ll have to do better.Â As the battle proceeds, OBI-WAN and COUNT DOOKU are tired. ANAKIN is stronger as he becomes angry. ANAKIN continues to drive the attack on DOOKU. COUNT DOOKU throws OBI-WAN back using the Force.Â ANAKIN and COUNT DOOKU move up the stairs. As they reach the upper landing of the General&#39;s Quarters, ANAKIN leaps over COUNT DOOKU. OBI-WAN reaches the top of the stairs, destroying TWO SUPER BATTLE DROIDS. COUNT DOOKU holds OBI-WAN in the air using the Force as he turns and kicks ANAKIN out of frame. OBI-WAN is choking.Â ANAKIN hits the archway.Â DOOKU sends OBI-WAN flying. The Jedi tumbles to the lower level unconscious. COUNT DOOKU spins around again and, using the Force, causes a section of the balcony to drop onto OBI-WAN. ANAKIN spins and kicks COUNT DOOKU, sending him over the balcony. ANAKIN Jumps, following him down to the main floor. COUNT DOOKU and ANAKIN continue the fight.Â COUNT DOOKU: (continuing) I sense great fear in you, Skywalker. You have hate, you have angerbut you donâ€™t use them.Â Anakin regains his composure and attacks COUNT DOOKU as the Dark Lord continues his spin to meet him head on. Their fighting becomes even more intense.Â Anakin attacks COUNT DOOKU with a new ferociousness.Â 39 INT. GENERAL&#39;S QUARTERS-TRADE FEDERATION CRUISERÂ Anakin and Dooku continue their fight. It is intense! Finally, in one last energized charge, ANAKIN cuts off COUNT DOOKU&#39;s hands. The Jedi catches the lightsaber as it drops from the severed Sith Lord&#39;s hand. COUNT DOOKU stumbles to the floor as ANAKIN puts the two lightsabers to his neck. PALPATINE is grinning as he watches COUNT DOOKU&#39;s defeat.Â PALPATINE: Good, Anakin, good. I knew you could do it. Kill him. Kill him now!Â ANAKIN: I shouldn&#39;t . . .Â PALPATINE: Do it!!Â ANAKIN cuts off COUNT DOOKU&#39;s head. A huge EXPLOSION somewhere deep in the ship rattles everything.Â ANAKIN: ... I couldn&#39;t stop myself.Â PALPATINE: You did well, Anakin. He was too dangerous to be kept alive.Â ANAKIN drops COUNT DOOKU&#39;s lightsaber, moving to PALPATINE.Â ANAKIN: Yesbut he was an unarmed prisoner.Â ANAKIN raises his hands toward PALPATINE, who is strapped in the Admiral&#39;s Chair. The Chancellor&#39;s restraints pop loose.Â ANAKIN: (continuing) I shouldn&#39;t have done that, Chancellor. It&#39;s not the Jedi way.Â PALPATINE stands up, rubbing his wrists.Â PALPATINE: It is only natural. He cut off your arm, and you wanted revenge. It wasn&#39;t the first time, Anakin. Remember what you told me about your mother and the Sand People. Now, we must leave before more security droids arrive.Â The ship begins to list to one side. ANAKIN rushes over to OBI-WAN, lifts the control console from on top of him, and pulls him free. He kneels down and checks out his unconscious friend. PALPATINE heads for the elevators.Â PALPATINE: (continuing) Anakin, there is no time. We must get off the ship before it&#39;s too late.Â ANAKIN: He seems to be all right. No broken bones, breathing&#39;s all right.Â PALPATINE: Leave him, or we&#39;ll never make it.Â ANAKIN: His fate will be the same as ours.Â ANAKIN picks up OBI-WAN, slings him over his shoulder, and heads for the elevators.Â 40 INT. BRIDGE-TRADE FEDERATION CRUISERÂ GENERAL GRIEVOUS: Prepare for attack.Â PILOT: All batteries fire! Fire!Â 41 INT. BATTLESTATIONS-REPUBLIC CRUISERÂ Clone gunners fire on the Trade Federation cruiser and take fire in return. Gun emplacements are destroyed. Clone troopers go flying.Â 42 INT. ELEVATOR LOBBY-GENERAL&#39;S QUARTERS-TRADE FEDERATION CRUISERÂ ANAKIN carries OBI-WAN to the elevator doors and hits the button. PALPATINE joins him.Â ANAKIN: The elevator&#39;s not working, (into his comlink) Artoo . . .Â ARTOO BEEPS a response to ANAKIN.Â ANAKIN: (continuing) . . . Activate Elevator 3224.Â Suddenly the ship shifts to its side as the elevator doors open. PALPATINE is thrown to the ground. ANAKIN jumps to the door frame of the elevator. ANAKIN looks into the elevator shaft.Â ANAKIN: (continuing) Artoo ... do you copy? Artoo, come in!Â 43 INT. BRIDGE-TRADE FEDERATION CRUISERÂ Windows are blown out, droids and equipment are sucked into space.Â PILOT: Reverse stabilizers.Â 44 INT. MAIN HANGAR-TRADE FEDERATION CRUISERÂ As the ship rolls, spacecraft and equipment CRASH from one side of the ship to the other.Â Several objects break through the metal blast doors, causing objects to be sucked into space. ARTOO starts to slide toward one of the small holes.Â 45 INT. ELEVATOR LOBBY-GENERAL&#39;S QUARTERS-TRADE FEDERATION CRUISERÂ As the elevator shaft rotates, it has become a long hallway.Â ANAKIN clings to the doorframe with OBI-WAN on his shoulder, as the Chancellor struggles to join him.Â 46 INT. MAIN HANGAR-TRADE FEDERATION CRUISERÂ ARTOO continues to skid and slide toward open space. He swerves around boxes and wrecked fighters. One of the BATTLE DROIDS stumbles and is consumed by the electronic shield in a zap. ARTOO BEEPS a reply as he dodges the laser blasts of the BATTLE DROIDS. One bolt hits very near him, and he SCREAMS in terror.Â 47 INT. BRIDGE-TRADE FEDERATION CRUISERÂ PILOT: Magnetize! Magnetize!Â 48 INT. MAIN HANGAR-TRADE FEDERATION CRUISERÂ ARTOO is about to be overtaken by a starfighter sliding behind him. He falls into a heap of broken battle droid parts and the fighter bounces over him.Â 49 EXT. SPACE-CORUSCANTÂ The TRADE FEDERATION CRUISER heads straight down toward the planet.Â 50 INT. ELEVATOR LOBBY-GENERAL&#39;S QUARTERS-TRADE FEDERATION CRUISERÂ ANAKIN jumps into the horizontal elevator shaft with OBI-WAN still on his shoulder.Â ANAKIN: We can&#39;t wait. Come on, we have to be fast.Â PALPATINE climbs into the elevator shaft also. They start running. The ship begins to roll again, and the Jedi and the Chancellor are forced to jump from one side of the elevator to the other.Â 51 INT. BRIDGE-TRADE FEDERATION CRUISERÂ GENERAL GRIEVOUS: Fire the emergency booster engines.Â PILOT: Leveling out, sir.Â 52 INT. ELEVATOR SHAFT ON SIDE-TRADE FEDERATION CRUISERÂ ANAKIN still carrying OBI-WAN on his back, and PALPATINE run down the elevator shaft as it starts to move upright. ANAKIN cuts a control box on one of the doorsbut before the doors can open, the ship moves to an angle, causing ANAKIN and PALPATINE to start sliding down the shaft. ANAKIN grabs some wires in the control box with one hand. PALPATINE grabs onto the Jedi&#39;s leg. As the ship rights itself, they are left hanging in the bottomless elevator shaft.Â 53 INT. ELEVATOR SHAFT, VERTICAL-TRADE FEDERATION CRUISERÂ ANAKIN, OBI-WAN, and PALPATINE hang precariously on the side of the bottomless elevator shaft. OBI-WAN regains consciousness and tries to look around.Â ANAKIN: Easy. . . . We&#39;re in a bit of a situation.Â OBI-WAN: Did I miss something?Â OBI-WAN looks down and sees PALPATINE and the bottomless pit. They hear ARTOO BEEPING on Obi-Wan&#39;s comlink. The ship begins to roll, causing the vertical shaft to move into a forty-five-degree angle. They hear the elevator brakes release and look up to see the elevator heading toward them.Â ANAKINN: Hold on.Â OBI-WAN: What is that?Â OBI-WAN and ANAKIN look up to watch the elevator approach them at high speed, then OBI-WAN turns to ANAKIN.Â OBI-WAN: (continuing) Oops.Â ANAKIN: Artoo, Artoo, shut down the elevator!Â OBI-WAN: Too late! Jump!Â They fall about three hundred feet before the tilt of the ship catches up with them, and they hit the side of the shaft and slide at great speed just ahead of the elevator. The shaft continues to rotate until it is completely horizontal.Â ANAKIN and OBI-WAN take out and throw grappling hooks. The hooks catch and they continue to fall. All the doors in the elevator shaft open up, and the group swings through the open door into a hallway. The elevator roars by.Â ",
            "textOriginal": "                 A long time ago in a galaxy far, far away.Â A vast sea of stars serves as the backdrop for the Main Title, followed by a rollup, which crawls into infinity.Â War! The Republic is crumbling under attacks by the ruthless Sith Lord, Count Dooku. There are heroes on both sides. Evil is everywhere.Â In a stunning move, the fiendish droid leader, General Grievous, has swept into the Republic capital and kidnapped Chancellor Palpatine, leader of the Galactic Senate.Â As the Separatist Droid Army attempts to flee the besieged capital with their valuable hostage, two Jedi Knights lead a desperate mission to rescue the captive Chancellor. . . .Â PAN DOWN to reveal a REPUBLIC ATTACK CRUISER. Continue to PAN with the Cruiser as TWO JEDI STARFIGHTERS enter and head toward an enemy Battle Cruiser. TRUCK with the Jedi Fighters as they maneuver in unison, dodging flack and enemy laser fire. R2-D2 is on Anakin's ship. R4-P17 is on Obi-Wan's ship. A giant space battle is revealed as the tiny Jedi ships continue their assault in a synchronous ballet.Â 2 INT. OBI-WAN'S STARFIGHTER COCKPIT-SPACEÂ OBI-WAN bounces through the flack with a frown. His ship rocks violently.Â 3 INT. ANAKINS STARFIGHTER COCKPIT-SPACEÂ ANAKIN smiles as he blasts a TRADE FEDERATION DROID DROP FIGHTER.Â ANAKIN: There isn't a droid made that can out fly you, Master, and no other way to get to the Chancellor . . .Â OBI-WAN: Look out, four droids inbound . . .Â 4 EXT. CORUSCANT-SPACE BATTLEÂ The TWO JEDI FIGHTERS swerve in unison as FOUR TRADE FEDERATION DROID DROP FIGHTERS attack. After several clever moves by the Jedi, two of the FEDERATION DROID DROP FIGHTERS collide with each other in a ball of flame.Â 5 INT. OBI-WAN'S STARFIGHTER COCKPIT-SPACEÂ OBI-WAN struggles to maintain control of his ship.Â OBI-WAN: We've got to split them up.Â ANAKIN: Break left, fly through the guns on that tower.Â OBI-WAN flies to the left of a huge tower on a REPUBLIC CRUISER. The TWO DROID DROP FIGHTERS follow.Â OBI-WAN: Easy for you to say . . . why am I always the bait?Â ANAKIN: Don't worry. I'm coming around behind you.Â OBI-WAN deftly maneuvers around a large Starship's superstructurebut the TWO DROID FIGHTERS stay on his tail, BLASTING him with intense laser fire.Â OBI-WAN: Anakin, they're all over me!Â ANAKIN: Dead ahead! Closing . . . lock onto him, Artoo . . .Â ARTOO BEEPS his reply as ANAKIN swoops in for the kill. ANAKIN BLASTS one of the DROID DROP FIGHTERS. It EXPLODES.Â ANAKIN: (continuing, laughs) We got him, Artoo!Â ANAKIN BLASTS away at the second DROID DROP FIGHTER as ARTOO BEEPS an angry warning.Â ANAKIN: I copy, Artoo.Â OBI-WAN: I'm going down on the deck.Â ANAKIN: Good idea ... I need some room to maneuver.Â OBI-WAN dives toward the surface of one of the larger TRADE FEDERATION BATTLESHIPS and is forced to fly through a maelstrom of laser flack. He skims the surface, followed by the DROID DROP FIGHTER, which is followed by ANAKIN.Â ANAKIN: (continuing) Cut right. Do you hear me?! Cut right. Don't let him get a handle on you. Come on, Artoo, lock on! Lock on!Â ARTOO BEEPS. The crosshairs merge on the DROID DROP FIGHTER.Â OBI-WAN: Hurry up! I don't like this!Â OBI-WAN flies through a narrow gap between two towers on a Battleship. The DROID DROP FIGHTER hits one of Obi-Wan's wings with a laser blast, and parts of the ship go flying around Obi-Wan's Astro Droid, ARFOUR.Â OBI-WAN: (continuing) Ouch!Â R-4 BEEPS a blue streak.Â OBI-WAN: (continuing) Don't even try to fix it, Arfour. I've shut it down.Â ANAKIN: We're locked on ... we've got him . . .Â ANAKIN drops in behind the DROID DROP FIGHTER and blows him apart. ARTOO SQUEALS with delight.Â ANAKIN: (continuing) Yeah! We got him . . . good going, Artoo.OBI-WAN: Next time you're the bait . . . Now let's find the Command Ship and get on with it ...Â R-4 BEEPS a blue streak.Â ANAKIN: Lock onto them, Artoo. Master, General Grievous's ship is directly ahead.Â ARTOO BEEPS a reply, and it re